### README

Nginx configuration (see nginx.conf)
to run Aegir Hosting System for Drupal
without the need to restart/reload
your fast, small and powerful webserver.

In this example (nginx.conf) Nginx is listening
on port 88 since port 80 is used by Pound/Nginx
load balancer or Varnish/Ncache fast proxy.


### REQUIREMENTS

* Latest 0.8.x nginx build - see nginx-install.txt

* php-fpm 5.2.11 - see php-fpm-install.txt


### AEGIR ADD-ONS

* provision.patch is required to run Aegir on nginx
  (for Aegir 0.4 alpha3)

* Please remember to use '/bin/true' for Apache
  restart command during Aegir installation.


### HELP

* see http://groups.drupal.org/nginx


